Others: San Antonio Spurs lost to Milwaukee Bucks with a score of 121-105.
The Bucks never trailed the Spurs during the game.
Victor Wembanyama scored 10 points, made 4-of-10 field goal attempts, and 2-of-6 three-point attempts.
Wembanyama had 10 rebounds and blocked 3 shots, but finished with a -7 plus-minus stat.
Damian Lillard led the Bucks with 26 points, Giannis Antetokounmpo was next with 25, and Brook Lopez had 22.
Milwaukee's other two starters, Taurean Prince and Andre Jackson, had a combined three points scored.
Milwaukee had a 47.8 field goal percentage compared to San Antonio's 36.8 field goal percentage.
